name: Thai Pork and Lime Stir Fry
description: A vibrant stir fry combining the tang of lime with savory pork and fresh vegetables.
tips: Serve with rice for a complete meal.

name: Malaysian Seafood Curry
description: A rich and spicy seafood curry made with a mix of prawns, squid, and mussels in coconut milk.
tips: Serve with steamed rice to soak up the flavorful sauce.

name: Scotch Eggs
description: Hard-boiled eggs wrapped in sausage meat, coated in breadcrumbs, and deep-fried.
tips: Serve warm with a side of mixed greens or your favorite dipping sauce.

name: Mexican Aguachile
description: A spicy and refreshing dish featuring shrimp marinated in lime juice with chili peppers, onions, and cucumbers.
tips: Serve immediately with tortilla chips for dipping.

name: Prawn Thai Salad with Peanut Dressing
description: A vibrant Thai salad with fresh prawns, mixed greens, and a spicy peanut dressing.
tips: Toss gently to combine all ingredients evenly before serving.

name: Nasi Goreng
description: Indonesian fried rice served with pieces of chicken and shrimp, flavored with chili and soy sauce.
tips: Garnish with fried shallots and serve with a side of pickles and chili sauce.

name: Mango Cream Cake
description: A delightful sponge cake filled with mango puree and topped with whipped cream and fresh mango slices.
tips: Chill before serving to set the cream.

name: Mini Lychee Tart Tatin
description: A delightful twist on the classic tart tatin, featuring caramelized lychees under a layer of puff pastry.
tips: Serve warm with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.

name: Chocolate Pikelets
description: Soft and fluffy mini pancakes infused with cocoa and studded with chocolate chips.
tips: Serve warm with a dollop of whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

name: Chai Tiramisu with Vanilla and Rum
description: An innovative take on the classic tiramisu, infused with chai tea and enhanced with vanilla and rum flavors.
tips: Allow to set in the fridge for several hours or overnight for best flavor infusion.

name: Jaggery Cheesecake
description: A rich and creamy cheesecake made with jaggery instead of sugar, offering a unique caramel-like flavor.
tips: Chill thoroughly before serving to enhance the flavors.

name: Mussels and 'Nduja
description: A spicy and flavorful dish featuring mussels cooked with 'Nduja, garlic, shallots, and white wine.
tips: Serve with crusty bread to soak up the flavorful sauce.

name: Cheesy Lasagne
description: A rich and hearty lasagne layered with cheese, ground beef, and a savory tomato sauce.
tips: Allow to rest for 10 minutes after baking for easier slicing.

name: Peanut Caramel Tart
description: A decadent tart featuring a rich caramel layer topped with roasted peanuts and dark chocolate.
tips: Allow the tart to cool completely in the fridge to set the caramel before serving.

name: Roast Pork Belly with Chargrilled Peach Salsa
description: Succulent roast pork belly paired with a fresh and zesty chargrilled peach salsa.
tips: Ensure the pork belly skin is scored for optimal crispiness.

name: Pistachio and Rose Halva
description: A traditional Middle Eastern sweet treat made with tahini and pistachios, flavored with rose water and cardamom.
tips: Store in an airtight container to maintain freshness.

name: Choc Malt Tiramisu
description: A twist on the classic tiramisu with layers of malted milk and chocolate flavors.
tips: Chill for at least 4 hours before serving to allow the flavors to meld.

name: Honey Vinegar Pie with Spiced Whipped Cream
description: A unique pie featuring a sweet and tangy filling topped with spiced whipped cream.
tips: Whip the cream just before serving to ensure it stays fluffy.

name: Monkfish with Kohlrabi, Cauliflower, and Dates
description: A refined dish featuring tender monkfish paired with a flavorful mix of kohlrabi, cauliflower, and sweet dates.
tips: Serve immediately to enjoy the freshness of the ingredients.

name: Green Tea Ice Cream
description: Creamy and refreshing ice cream flavored with matcha green tea powder.
tips: Serve immediately after churning for best texture or freeze for later use.

name: Porcini Mushroom Soup
description: A rich and earthy soup made with porcini and assorted fresh mushrooms, infused with thyme.
tips: Serve hot with crusty bread for a hearty meal.

name: Spaghetti with Pipis
description: A delightful seafood pasta featuring fresh pipis (clams) tossed with spaghetti in a garlicky, tomato-based sauce.
tips: Ensure pipis are fully cleaned to remove any sand before cooking.

name: Banh Mi
description: A Vietnamese sandwich that includes a crispy baguette filled with pork, fresh vegetables, and vibrant condiments.
tips: Toast the baguette lightly to add extra crunch.

name: Stuffed Pork Tenderloin
description: Succulent pork tenderloin stuffed with feta, spinach, and sun-dried tomatoes, seasoned with fresh herbs.
tips: Ensure the pork is evenly stuffed and secured to maintain shape during cooking.

name: Roast Beef with Caramelized Onion Gravy
description: Tender roast beef served with a rich and flavorful gravy made from caramelized onions and a hint of balsamic vinegar.
tips: Rest the beef after roasting to ensure it retains its juices when sliced.

name: Miso-Maple Braised Leeks
description: Leeks braised in a savory-sweet sauce made from miso and maple syrup, enriched with fresh garlic and ginger.
tips: Serve as a side dish or incorporate into vegetarian main courses.

name: Apple Tarte Tatin
description: A delicious caramelized apple tart baked with puff pastry.
tips: Serve warm with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.

name: Pan-Fried Halibut with Cockles and Peanuts
description: A pan-fried halibut dish with cockles and a peanut topping.
tips: Garnish with chopped parsley and a squeeze of lemon.

name: Roast Chicken
description: A perfectly roasted chicken with garlic, lemon, and thyme.
tips: Let the chicken rest before carving for best flavor.

name: Beef Stroganoff
description: A creamy dish with sautéed beef strips and mushrooms, served over noodles or rice.
tips: Garnish with parsley and serve with mashed potatoes or noodles.

name: Shrimp Paella
description: A traditional Spanish rice dish with shrimp, saffron, and mixed vegetables.
tips: Use seafood stock for more flavor and add lemon wedges for garnish.

name: Vegetarian Chili
description: A hearty chili made with a mix of beans, tomatoes, and spices.
tips: Top with avocado slices and grated cheese for extra flavor.

name: Mushroom Risotto
description: A creamy risotto cooked with mushrooms and vegetable broth, topped with Parmesan cheese.
tips: Stir continuously for a creamy consistency.

name: Lamb Tagine
description: A slow-cooked Moroccan lamb stew with dried fruits and spices.
tips: Serve with couscous or flatbread.

name: Chicken Alfredo
description: A creamy pasta dish with chicken, fettuccine, and Parmesan cheese.
tips: Top with parsley and a pinch of black pepper for extra flavor.

name: Fish Tacos
description: Grilled white fish served in tortillas with fresh toppings like cabbage, avocado, and lime.
tips: Squeeze some extra lime juice on top for an extra tangy flavor.

name: Stuffed Bell Peppers
description: Bell peppers stuffed with ground beef, rice, and topped with melted cheese.
tips: Use different colored peppers for a more vibrant presentation.

name: Eggplant Parmesan
description: Breaded and fried eggplant layered with cheese and tomato sauce, then baked.
tips: Serve with a side of pasta for a complete meal.

name: Butternut Squash Soup
description: A creamy soup made from roasted butternut squash and vegetable broth.
tips: Garnish with a drizzle of cream and fresh thyme leaves.

name: Beef and Broccoli Stir Fry
description: A quick stir fry of beef strips and broccoli in a savory soy sauce.
tips: Serve over steamed rice or noodles for a complete meal.

name: Lemon Bars
description: A tart and sweet dessert made with lemon curd on a buttery crust.
tips: Dust with powdered sugar before serving for extra flavor.

name: Chicken Caesar Salad
description: A classic Caesar salad with grilled chicken, Parmesan cheese, and croutons.
tips: Drizzle Caesar dressing just before serving to keep the salad fresh.

name: Vegetarian Lasagna
description: Layers of lasagna noodles, ricotta cheese, and spinach topped with mozzarella cheese.
tips: Let the lasagna cool before slicing to ensure neat portions.

name: Shrimp Scampi
description: Sautéed shrimp in garlic butter, with lemon and white wine.
tips: Serve with fresh parsley and a wedge of lemon.

name: Beef Tacos
description: A savory taco filled with seasoned ground beef, lettuce, and cheese.
tips: Top with salsa and guacamole for extra flavor.

name: Pesto Pasta
description: Pasta tossed with a fresh basil pesto sauce, topped with Parmesan cheese.
tips: Garnish with cherry tomatoes for added color and flavor.

name: Salmon with Asparagus
description: Grilled salmon fillet served with roasted asparagus and lemon wedges.

name: Egg Salad Sandwich
description: A sandwich filled with chopped eggs and mayonnaise served on toasted bread.
tips: Add some lettuce for a fresh crunch.

name: Salmon Teriyaki
description: Salmon glazed with a sweet and savory teriyaki sauce.
tips: Serve with steamed rice and garnish with sesame seeds.

name: Pumpkin Pie
description: A spiced pumpkin filling baked in a buttery crust.
tips: Serve with a dollop of whipped cream for extra flavor.

name: Chicken Enchiladas
description: Baked tortillas filled with chicken and cheese, topped with enchilada sauce.
tips: Top with fresh cilantro before serving for extra flavor.

name: Egg Fried Rice
description: Stir-fried rice with eggs and mixed vegetables, seasoned with soy sauce.
tips: Add a touch of sesame oil at the end for extra aroma.

name: Pasta Primavera
description: A light pasta dish with fresh vegetables and Parmesan cheese.
tips: Garnish with basil leaves and a drizzle of olive oil before serving.
